# Rent History Analyzer Shared Rules

## Non-overridable directives
- Preserve API contract integrity across `auth-provider`, `rent-history`, and `rh-extract`.
- For backend API changes, regenerate and commit `auth-provider/rh/openapi/openapi.json` in the same change.
- Do not bypass required CI checks or remove contract validation safeguards.

## Plan-mode clarification policy
- In plan mode, ask 1-2 targeted clarification questions whenever requirements are ambiguous or a choice changes implementation materially.
- Ask clarifying questions before finalizing the plan and before coding when unresolved assumptions remain.
- Prefer defaults only for low-risk details and state those defaults explicitly.

## Cross-repo coordination
- When a change affects API fields/endpoints/auth, include impact notes for both `rent-history` and `rh-extract`.
- Keep documentation and checklists synchronized with behavior changes.

## Local override boundary
- Developers may add local preference rules for tone/format/workflow speed.
- Local overrides must not conflict with non-overridable directives above.
